description: Commit, PR, and branch conventions for Quem Pega Quem. Always apply. The full conventions live under ai/conventions/.
alwaysApply: true
---

Follow the conventions documented in:

- `ai/conventions/commits.md` — Conventional Commits with the project
  scope table.
- `ai/conventions/prs.md` — PR title shape, body template, Risk
  Checklist usage, and the stacked-PR pattern.
- `ai/conventions/branches.md` — branch naming.

Quick reference:

- Commit / PR title shape: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`.
- Subject is imperative mood, lower-case, no trailing period, ≤ 72
  chars.
- Branches: `<type>/<short-kebab-description>`. No personal prefixes,
  no ticket numbers, no `wip/`.
- Stacked PRs encode the dependency through the base branch, not
  through name suffixes like `[1/N]`.
- Risk Checklist tickboxes need evidence in the Summary or Notes.
- Co-authoring with AI: include `Co-Authored-By:` naming the tool.

Read the full convention files when in doubt — they are short and
they hold the *why*.
